      "content": "The most common counter-arguments fundamentally challenge the notion of absolute sovereignty in a globalized world. Critics argue that rigid border enforcement violates universal human rights, suggesting that the right to seek asylum supersedes any national border control. Another frequent rebuttal posits that the concept of \"rule of law\" should prioritize humanitarian obligations over strict legal enforcement. These arguments often frame strict policies as inherently inhumane and incompatible with modern international ethics.",
